Adcock Ingram Aiming to Increase Liquids Production, Business Report Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-03-18T05:23:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/adcock-ingram-aiming-to-increase-liquids-production-business-report-says.html
  Adcock Ingram Holdings Ltd. (AIP)  plans
to more than double liquids production as part of a 1.5 billion
rand expansion,  Business Report  said, citing Chief Executive
Officer Jonathan Louw.  The drugmaker currently has about 50 percent of the South
African liquids market with production of about 8 million to 9
million liters a year, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.
Adcock aims to boost output to about 24 million liters a year
and increase exports to other parts of  Africa , Business Report
said, citing Louw.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  